The paper proposes a new memory structure for reinforcement learning algorithms, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed structure aims to improve the efficiency of training the reinforcement learning agent, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The experiments are conducted on environments from OpenAI Gym, which is a popular platform for reinforcement learning research and often used in computer vision (cs.CV) tasks.
